               <p>EIGHTH DAY. FRIDAY, JUNE 8.</p>
               <p>Third London Jury - Before Mr. Sergeant Arabin.</p>
               <p>1343. 
               <persName id="t18270531-330-defend1774" type="defendantName">
                  ELIZABETH 
                  JORDAN
               <interp inst="t18270531-330-defend1774" type="surname" value="JORDAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-defend1774" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-defend1774" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-defend1774" type="age" value="21"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t18270531-330-off1772" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-off1772" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-off1772" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18270531-330-cd1773" type="crimeDate">2d of June</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-330-off1772 t18270531-330-cd1773"></join>, 1 watch, value 2l. 10s.; 1 seal, value 1l. 1s.; 1 watch-key, value 10s.; 1 gold ring, value 10s.; and 1 watch-ribbon, value 1d., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18270531-330-victim1775" type="victimName">
                        Charles 
                        Wales
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-victim1775" type="surname" value="Wales"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18270531-330-victim1775" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18270531-330-victim1775" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-330-off1772 t18270531-330-victim1775"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>CHARLES WALES. I am a <rs id="t18270531-330-viclabel1774" type="occupation">painter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-330-victim1775 t18270531-330-viclabel1774"></join>, and live with my father, in Gravel-lane. About two o'clock in the morning of the 2d of June, I was returning from the theatre - I had had some refreshment, but I was sober; the prisoner accosted me on Ludgate-hill and asked me to treat her; I asked what she meant, she said, "Give me something to drink," I walked to the corner of <placeName id="t18270531-330-crimeloc1775">Bridge-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-330-crimeloc1775" type="placeName" value="Bridge-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-330-crimeloc1775" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-330-off1772 t18270531-330-crimeloc1775"></join>, and stood talking with her for two or three minutes. I saw her with my watch in her hand, and she put it into her bosom. I accused her of it - the watchman came up and took her to the watch-house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-330-person1776">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SINGLETON
               <interp inst="t18270531-330-person1776" type="surname" value="SINGLETON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-person1776" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-person1776" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I saw the prisoner and prosecutor together, talking, at the corner of Bridge-street, the prosecutor had hold of her, and asked for his watch. I took her to the watch-house; the officer found it in her bosom.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-330-person1777">
                  JOSEPH 
                  STRIBLEHILL
               <interp inst="t18270531-330-person1777" type="surname" value="STRIBLEHILL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-person1777" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-person1777" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was officer of the night - The prisoner was brought to the watch-house in custody; the prosecutor appeared sober; I searched the prisoner - this watch was in her bosom.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-330-person1778">
                  HENRY 
                  BOLTON
               <interp inst="t18270531-330-person1778" type="surname" value="BOLTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-person1778" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-person1778" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was watch-house-keeper. I saw the prisoner take this watch from her bosom; she had been charged with stealing it, and denied it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. He went home with me, and afterwards to several public-houses - he gave me his watch as a pledge; I refused to return it, and he called the watchman.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270531-330-verdict1776" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-verdict1776" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 21.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270531-330-punish1777" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270531-330-punish1777" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-330-defend1774 t18270531-330-punish1777"></join>
               Transported for Life
            </rs>.</p>
